Program 1- Write a program to calculate the average of 5 numbers.
Answer:
<html>
<head>
            <title>Average of 5 numbers entered</title>
</head>
<body>
           <script>
                  Var sum = 0;
                  Var n;
                   Var txt = “Average of numbers  :  “ ;
                   For(Var i=0; i<5; i++)
                   {
                                n = parseInt(prompt(“Enter the number”, “0”));
                                sum = sum + n;
                                txt + = n + “ “ ;
                   }
                  Document.write(txt + “  is  <B>”  +  (sum/5)  +  “</B>”)
                 </script>
</body>
</html>

Program 2- Write a program to calculate the sum of 5 numbers.
Answer:
<html>
<body>
<script>
             Var I, n=5, sum=0;
             arr = new Array(10, 12, 13, 15, 19);
            for(i=0;  i<5;  i++)
                   sum = sum + arr[i];
          document.write(sum);
</script>
</body>
</html>

Program 3- Write a program that accepts two strings (firstName and lastName) and print final string on the console.
Answer:
<html>
<body>
<p id = “demo”></p>
<script>
Const myObject = {
             firstName : “Rahul”,
             lastName : “Sharma”,
             fullName : function()  {
                         return this.firstName + “ “ + this.lastName;
          }
      }
Document.getElementById(“demo”).innerHTML = myObject.fullName();
</script>
</body>
</html>

Program 4- Write a function that accepts interest, principle, and tenure and calculates EMI.
Answer
<html>
<body>
<script>
Function emi_calculator(p, i, t)
{
     Let emi;
     r = r / (12 * 100);
     t = t * 12;
     emi = (p * i * Math.power(1 + i, t )) / (Math.pow( 1 + i, t ) – 1 );
return (emi + 0.00414);
}
let  principal, interest, tenure, emi ;
principal = 10000;
interest = 10;
tenure = 2;
emi = emi_caculator(principal, interest, tenure);
document.write(“Monthly EMI Is = “ + emi.toFixed(6));
</script>
</body>
</html>

Program 5- Print even numbers from 0-100
Answer 
Let i
Let a = 100
Console.log(“All even numbers from 0 to 100”)
For ( i = 0; i<=a ; i++)
{
     If(I % 2 == 0){ 
           Console.log(i)
     }
}

Program 6- Print odd numbers from 0-100
Answer
Let i
Let a = 100
Console.log(“All even numbers from 0 to 100”)
For ( i = 0; i<=a ; i++)
{
     If(I % 2 !== 0){ 
           Console.log(i)
     }
}

Program 7- Create an array of length 5 and store below numbers 
       1,11,111,222,555 . Write a program to calculate the average of numbers.
Answer

<Script>
  
          function average (a, n)
          {
                     Var Sum = 0;
                      For (Var I = 0; I < n; i++) Sum + = a[i];
                      Return parseFloat(Sum / n);
          }

          Var arr = [1, 11, 111, 222, 555];
           Var n = arr.write(“<br>”);
</script>


Program 8- Write a program that creates the below Object.
	Object name - Student
	Property 
		Name
		College Name
		Location
		PinCode
		Teachers details should be teacherName, teacherPhone, teacherSubjects

	Print Student name, teacherName on console.
Answer

function Student (name, college_Name, location, pincode) {

   // assigning  parameter values to the calling object
    this.name = name,
    this.college =  college_Name,
    this.location = location,
    this.pincode =pincode,

    this.greet = function () {
        return ('Hi' + ' ' + this.name);
    }
    
}

function Teacher (name, college_Name, location, pincode) {

